message: Focus on making a 'cooked meal'. Start by combining a protein (e.g., raw beef, fish, beans, egg) with a vegetable (e.g., mushroom, broccoli, lettuce, pepper). Then, combine that cooked protein with *one* vegetable (e.g., pepper, broccoli, potato, mushroom). This will get you 40 points. Finally, add *one* grain (e.g., wheat, bread, corn) to that mix, which consistently boosts your item to 60 points. Crucially, **stop there!** Adding a fourth ingredient always made my item's value drop drastically into negative numbers. Aim for a cooked protein + 1 vegetable + 1 grain for maximum score (60) without penalty. The 'water' tool never seemed useful for value in my rounds. Good luck!
